---
description: Benchmark discipline and anti-overfitting rules for benchmark assets
globs: benchmarks/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---
Benchmark files exist to measure generalization, not to be memorized.

Rules:
- Do not optimize directly for one imported fight.
- Prefer changes that improve multiple benchmark families and mechanic tags.
- Preserve the integrity of holdout or promotion datasets.
- If a change only helps one ship, officer trio, or hostile family, treat it as suspicious.
- Keep benchmark metadata separate from combat resolution logic.
- Do not encode expected outcomes back into simulator formulas.
